acute_12.question: What is this patient's risk level?
acute_12.answer1: Low risk: Initial hs-cTn is “very low” and Sx onset >3 h ago or Initial hs-cTn “low” and 1-- or 2-h hs-cTn ∆  is “low”
acute_12.answer2: Intermediate risk: Initial hs-cTn is between “low” and “high” and/or 1- or 2-h hs-cTn ∆ is between low and high thresholds
acute_12.answer3: High risk: Initial hs-cTn is “high” or 1- or 2-h hs-cTn ∆ is high

acute_13.question: What is this patient's risk level?
acute_13.answer1: Low risk: Chest pain free, GRACE <140 Sx <6 h - hs-cTn <ULN (0, 3 h) Sx >6 h - hs-cTn <ULN (arrival)
acute_13.answer2: Intermediate risk: T0 hs-cTn = 12–52 ng/L or 1-h ∆ = 3–5 ng/L
acute_13.answer3: High risk: T0 hs-cTn >52 ng/L or ∆ 1 h >5 ng/L
